00:06:59.460 --> 00:07:01.640
So let me start by
doing a little bit

00:07:01.640 --> 00:07:08.580
of dimensional analysis, just
to remind you important scales

00:07:08.580 --> 00:07:09.285
for the gravity.

00:07:20.350 --> 00:07:23.360
So the first thing is what
we called the Planck scale.

00:07:30.470 --> 00:07:43.890
So in nature we have
fundamental constant H-bar,

00:07:43.890 --> 00:07:49.030
Newton constant, and
the C, speed of light.

00:07:49.030 --> 00:07:57.050
And immediately after Planck
himself introduced this H-bar,

00:07:57.050 --> 00:08:00.740
he realized you can actually
combine the three of them

00:08:00.740 --> 00:08:09.605
to come up with a map scale,
which is just hc divided by GN.

00:08:09.605 --> 00:08:12.830
And this, if you plug in the
expressed numerical value,

00:08:12.830 --> 00:08:20.160
it's about 1.2 to the 10, to the
19 gev, divided by c squared.

00:08:20.160 --> 00:08:24.080
You can also write it in terms
of the gram, which is about 2.2

00:08:24.080 --> 00:08:26.940
10 to the minus 5 gram.

00:08:29.630 --> 00:08:32.440
And then you can also
have-- we can also

00:08:32.440 --> 00:08:41.390
construct the length scale,
which is hGN divide c cubed,

00:08:41.390 --> 00:08:46.110
which is about 1.6 to 10
the minus 33 centimeter.

00:08:51.590 --> 00:08:57.170
And tp equals lp
divided by c, OK?

00:09:00.400 --> 00:09:06.590
So this was discovered--
Planck introduced them

00:09:06.590 --> 00:09:12.270
in 1899, so most of
you may know the story.

00:09:12.270 --> 00:09:15.170
And then, just immediately
after he introduced H-bar-- so

00:09:15.170 --> 00:09:18.990
he introduced H-bar in 1899.

00:09:18.990 --> 00:09:25.110
In the same year he realized you
can write down those numbers.

00:09:25.110 --> 00:09:28.930
And of course, those
numbers meant nothing to him

00:09:28.930 --> 00:09:34.070
because at that time he didn't
know special relativity,

00:09:34.070 --> 00:09:37.410
he didn't know quantum
mechanics-- essentially,

00:09:37.410 --> 00:09:39.960
he didn't know anything.

00:09:39.960 --> 00:09:49.460
But he famously said
that this unit-- so he

00:09:49.460 --> 00:09:53.300
claimed those should be
basic units of physics,

00:09:53.300 --> 00:09:56.980
and he also said these
are the units that

00:09:56.980 --> 00:10:01.740
would retain their significance
for all times and all cultures.

00:10:05.320 --> 00:10:10.125
He even said they even
will apply to aliens.

00:10:15.220 --> 00:10:21.310
But only after 50 years--
so after 1950s people

00:10:21.310 --> 00:10:22.260
get some sense.

00:10:22.260 --> 00:10:25.530
So many years after
special relativity,

00:10:25.530 --> 00:10:27.790
many years after
general relativity,

00:10:27.790 --> 00:10:30.460
and also quantum mechanics,
et cetera, people

00:10:30.460 --> 00:10:35.700
started grasping the
meaning of those scales.

00:10:35.700 --> 00:10:38.630
And so let me
briefly review them.

00:10:42.450 --> 00:10:46.750
So you can-- OK, the feeling
of the meaning of those scales

00:10:46.750 --> 00:10:50.740
by looking at the
strength of gravity.

00:10:50.740 --> 00:10:54.981
So let me first start this
example for electromagnetism,

00:10:54.981 --> 00:10:57.340
which you have a
potential, which

00:10:57.340 --> 00:11:00.940
is e squared divided by r.

00:11:00.940 --> 00:11:04.150
So if you have two charged
particle of charge e,

00:11:04.150 --> 00:11:07.360
then the potential between
them is e squared divided by r.

00:11:11.350 --> 00:11:14.424
And then for particle
of mass m then

00:11:14.424 --> 00:11:15.840
you also have
Compton wavelengths.

00:11:20.560 --> 00:11:23.194
So if you have a
particle with mass m,

00:11:23.194 --> 00:11:24.610
you also have
Compton wavelengths.

00:11:24.610 --> 00:11:26.120
It's H-bar divided my mc.

00:11:28.820 --> 00:11:37.630
So you can get rough
measure of the strength

00:11:37.630 --> 00:11:40.850
of electromagnetism--
the actual strength

00:11:40.850 --> 00:11:45.940
of the electromagnetism
by conceiving

00:11:45.940 --> 00:11:49.980
the following [INAUDIBLE]
dimension number, which

00:11:49.980 --> 00:11:56.780
I call lambda e, which is
the potential evaluated

00:11:56.780 --> 00:11:59.600
at the minimal-- in
quantum mechanics,

00:11:59.600 --> 00:12:03.570
essentially this is the minimal
distance you can make sense of.

00:12:03.570 --> 00:12:05.570
Because once you go
distance smaller than these,

00:12:05.570 --> 00:12:08.770
you can no longer-- and
then the quantum uncertainty

00:12:08.770 --> 00:12:12.500
will create the energy
uncertainty bigger than m,

00:12:12.500 --> 00:12:17.680
and you can no longer
talk about single particle

00:12:17.680 --> 00:12:19.280
in a sensible way.

00:12:19.280 --> 00:12:21.260
So the essentially
the minimal length

00:12:21.260 --> 00:12:24.160
scale you can talk
about single particles.

00:12:24.160 --> 00:12:29.160
So this is essentially
some energy scale.

00:12:29.160 --> 00:12:31.880
So you can compare these to
the, say, the static mass

00:12:31.880 --> 00:12:33.360
of the particle.

00:12:33.360 --> 00:12:36.990
So this give you a
measure of the strength

00:12:36.990 --> 00:12:39.670
of electromagnetism.

00:12:39.670 --> 00:12:42.470
Of course, if you
plug this in you

00:12:42.470 --> 00:12:46.000
just get e squared
divided by H-bar c.

00:12:46.000 --> 00:12:49.150
And of course, we know this is
the fine structure constant,

00:12:49.150 --> 00:12:54.680
which is indeed the coupling.

00:12:54.680 --> 00:13:01.670
Say you would do-- indeed,
it's a coupling in QED, OK?

00:13:01.670 --> 00:13:04.777
So you can do the same
thing for gravity.

00:13:04.777 --> 00:13:06.360
You can do the same
thing for gravity.

00:13:15.120 --> 00:13:26.905
So for gravity we have
essentially g, and say

00:13:26.905 --> 00:13:28.550
if you take two
particle of masses

00:13:28.550 --> 00:13:34.720
m then the potential between
them is gm, m squared,

00:13:34.720 --> 00:13:37.120
divided by r.

00:13:37.120 --> 00:13:40.750
And then again, you can
define effective strength

00:13:40.750 --> 00:13:42.130
for the gravity.

00:13:42.130 --> 00:13:46.090
I evaluate this potential
at Compton wavelengths

00:13:46.090 --> 00:13:51.890
divided by the static
energy of the particle.

00:13:51.890 --> 00:13:54.570
And then you can
just plug this in.

00:13:54.570 --> 00:14:01.350
So this is GN m squared,
divided by H-bar, divided by mc,

00:14:01.350 --> 00:14:06.430
then divided by mc squared.

00:14:06.430 --> 00:14:16.970
And then you find this is just
equal to GN m squared, divided

00:14:16.970 --> 00:14:20.020
by H-bar c.

00:14:20.020 --> 00:14:27.490
OK, so now if you compare
with this equation--

00:14:27.490 --> 00:14:32.280
OK, so this is just given by m
squared divided by mp squared.

00:14:32.280 --> 00:14:40.590
OK, so for gravity
this effective strength

00:14:40.590 --> 00:14:44.460
is just given by the
mass of the particle.

00:14:44.460 --> 00:14:45.880
So because for
gravity the mass is

00:14:45.880 --> 00:14:47.730
like some kind of
effective charge,

00:14:47.730 --> 00:14:49.810
and then divided
by Planck scale--

00:14:49.810 --> 00:14:52.050
this Planck mass-- squared.

00:14:52.050 --> 00:15:06.190
OK, and you can also write
it as lp squared divided

00:15:06.190 --> 00:15:12.970
by rc squared, or just
as this Planck length

00:15:12.970 --> 00:15:16.740
divided by [INAUDIBLE]
wavelengths of this particle.

00:15:16.740 --> 00:15:23.350
OK, so for most
elementary particles--

00:15:23.350 --> 00:15:25.380
so for typical
elementary particles

00:15:25.380 --> 00:15:30.570
we know the m is always
much smaller than mp.

00:15:30.570 --> 00:15:37.270
And then the lambda g would be
typically much smaller than 1.

00:15:37.270 --> 00:15:44.500
So for example, say, if
you can see the electron,

00:15:44.500 --> 00:15:48.540
the electron mass
would be 5 to the 10

00:15:48.540 --> 00:15:53.870
to the minus 4 gev
divided by c squared.

00:15:53.870 --> 00:15:57.690
Of course this is much
smaller than this Planck mass.

00:15:57.690 --> 00:16:00.860
And then you find that
this ratio-- so you

00:16:00.860 --> 00:16:02.140
can work out this ratio.

00:16:02.140 --> 00:16:06.110
So let's compare it to
the corresponding strength

00:16:06.110 --> 00:16:08.070
for electromagnetism.

00:16:08.070 --> 00:16:14.730
So this is about 10 to the
minus 43 if you work this out.

00:16:14.730 --> 00:16:16.720
So this tells you the
gravity's really weak.

00:16:21.140 --> 00:16:27.690
So for ordinary
elementary particles--

00:16:27.690 --> 00:16:31.420
so the gravity is
really weak, and so we

00:16:31.420 --> 00:16:38.070
can forget all about gravity
until you reach the Planck

00:16:38.070 --> 00:16:41.620
mass, or your
Compton wavelengths

00:16:41.620 --> 00:16:44.110
reach the Planck length.

00:16:44.110 --> 00:16:49.815
And then the fact of the quantum
gravity will be important.

00:16:52.480 --> 00:16:57.540
So from this exercise we know
that the mp is the energy

00:16:57.540 --> 00:17:06.380
scale, that the effective
gravity strength become

00:17:06.380 --> 00:17:16.740
of order one-- become of order
one-- that is, quantum gravity

00:17:16.740 --> 00:17:25.606
fact becomes significant.

00:17:34.070 --> 00:17:45.474
And similarly-- so lp is the
corresponding length scale

00:17:45.474 --> 00:17:46.640
associated with such energy.

00:17:54.290 --> 00:17:59.360
So this give you a
heuristic feeling--

00:17:59.360 --> 00:18:02.730
give you a heuristic
indication that the meaning

00:18:02.730 --> 00:18:05.020
of those Planck scales.

00:18:05.020 --> 00:18:11.570
OK, so there's another important
scale associated with gravity.

00:18:11.570 --> 00:18:12.800
So any questions on this?

00:18:16.390 --> 00:18:20.380
Good, there's another important
scale associated with gravity.

00:18:20.380 --> 00:18:34.650
It's called Schwarzschild
radius-- Schwarzschild radius.

00:18:34.650 --> 00:18:37.320
So just from
dimensional analysis,

00:18:37.320 --> 00:18:41.070
the Schwarzschild radius
can be argued as follows.

00:18:41.070 --> 00:18:43.360
So can see that--
again, we can just even

00:18:43.360 --> 00:18:47.000
see from Newtonian gravity.

00:18:47.000 --> 00:18:54.490
So I would say let's consider
the object of mass m.

00:18:59.450 --> 00:19:09.170
Then we ask is the
distance-- at what distance,

00:19:09.170 --> 00:19:26.420
maybe I should-- at
what distance from it

00:19:26.420 --> 00:19:28.110
the classical gravity
becomes strong.

00:19:45.230 --> 00:19:49.240
So for this purpose,
let's consider,

00:19:49.240 --> 00:19:53.680
say, a probe mass--
say, m prime.

00:19:53.680 --> 00:19:54.865
So, can see the probe mass.

00:20:00.290 --> 00:20:04.910
So I define a scale
which I call rs,

00:20:04.910 --> 00:20:09.760
as I require the potential
energy between m and m prime.

00:20:09.760 --> 00:20:14.900
at such a scale rs, then
this become of order,

00:20:14.900 --> 00:20:21.550
say again, the static energy
of this probe political,

00:20:21.550 --> 00:20:24.390
or of this probe mass.

00:20:24.390 --> 00:20:26.830
So if you cancel
things out then you

00:20:26.830 --> 00:20:35.280
find rs is of order GNm
divided by c squared.

00:20:35.280 --> 00:20:46.780
OK, so this give you--
I'll give you a scale.

00:20:46.780 --> 00:20:51.350
You can also ask-- so this
is from Newtonian gravity.

00:20:51.350 --> 00:20:55.730
Of course, when your
gravity becomes strong

00:20:55.730 --> 00:20:58.090
you should replace
the Newtonian gravity

00:20:58.090 --> 00:21:01.530
by Einstein, the relativity.

00:21:01.530 --> 00:21:05.960
And then when you
go to relativity--

00:21:05.960 --> 00:21:10.040
when you go to relativity,
general relativity,

00:21:10.040 --> 00:21:14.170
then you find then there's
a Schwarzschild radius.

00:21:14.170 --> 00:21:16.070
So there's a
Schwarzschild radius

00:21:16.070 --> 00:21:22.130
which given by 2 gm divided by
c squared, which corresponding

00:21:22.130 --> 00:21:23.710
to the sides of a black hole.

00:21:30.340 --> 00:21:35.040
OK, corresponding to the
sides of a black hole.

00:21:35.040 --> 00:21:37.570
So this is a classical scale--
purely classical scale.

00:21:37.570 --> 00:21:39.390
Just the scale which
the classical gravity

00:21:39.390 --> 00:21:42.270
becomes strong.

00:21:42.270 --> 00:21:53.350
In particular, rs
can be considered

00:21:53.350 --> 00:22:20.040
as the minimal length scale one
can probe an object of mass m,

00:22:20.040 --> 00:22:22.870
OK?

00:22:22.870 --> 00:22:28.140
So classically, black
hole absorb everything.

00:22:28.140 --> 00:22:31.330
So once you fall into black
hole you can never come back.

00:22:31.330 --> 00:22:34.910
And so the minimal
distance you can

00:22:34.910 --> 00:22:39.820
approach an object of mass m,
it is given by the Schwarzschild

00:22:39.820 --> 00:22:40.654
radius.

00:22:40.654 --> 00:22:42.570
So when you go inside
the Schwarzschild radius

00:22:42.570 --> 00:22:44.186
we just fall into
the black hole,

00:22:44.186 --> 00:22:45.810
and you can never
send information out.

00:22:48.430 --> 00:22:51.967
And the one interesting
thing compare--

00:22:51.967 --> 00:22:54.300
yeah, one interesting thing
regarding this Schwarzschild

00:22:54.300 --> 00:22:55.720
radius.

00:22:55.720 --> 00:22:59.840
You said Schwarzschild
radius increase with mass.

00:22:59.840 --> 00:23:04.240
OK, if you increase the mass the
Schwarzschild radius increases.

00:23:04.240 --> 00:23:06.670
So in principal it
can be very large

00:23:06.670 --> 00:23:09.029
when you can see the very
large object-- when you can

00:23:09.029 --> 00:23:10.195
see the very massive object.

00:23:15.660 --> 00:23:17.585
So now-- so let us summarize.

00:23:21.650 --> 00:23:24.780
Let us summarize.

00:23:24.780 --> 00:23:37.040
So for object of mass m there
are two important scales.

00:23:42.270 --> 00:23:43.555
Two important scales.

00:23:51.980 --> 00:24:01.876
So one is just the standard
Compton wavelengths,

00:24:01.876 --> 00:24:03.625
and the other is the
Schwarzschild radius.

00:24:11.980 --> 00:24:15.440
So one is quantum and
the other is classical.

00:24:15.440 --> 00:24:17.310
The other is classical.

00:24:17.310 --> 00:24:20.750
So let's take the
ratio between them.

00:24:20.750 --> 00:24:22.484
Let's take the
ratio between them.

00:24:25.970 --> 00:24:31.710
So if you take the ratio
between them-- so let's

00:24:31.710 --> 00:24:37.212
forget about these two,
just to consider of order

00:24:37.212 --> 00:24:39.100
up to order 1.

00:24:39.100 --> 00:24:44.470
So c squared, divided
